  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">As a rule, an intensity spectrum of undulator radiation (UR) is calculated by using the classical approach, even for electron energy higher than 10 GeV. Such a spectrum is determined by an electron trajectory in an undulator while neglecting radiation loss. Using Planck’s law, the UR photon spectrum can be calculated from the obtained intensity spectrum, for both linear and nonlinear regimes.</subfield>
